trans-unit.source: Represents the C14N XML canonicalization transform for a digital signature as defined by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C), without comments.
trans-unit.target: Representerer C14N XML-adresser transformeringen for en digital signatur som er definert av World Wide Web Consortium (W3C), uten kommentarer.

trans-unit.source: The XmlDsigC14NTransform class represents the C14N XML canonicalization transform that describes the canonical form of an XML document.
trans-unit.target: Klassen XmlDsigC14NTransform representerer C14N XML-adresser transformeringen som beskriver kanoniske form av et XML-dokument.

trans-unit.source: This transform allows a signer to create a digest (used to create a digital signature) using the canonical form of an XML document.
trans-unit.target: Denne transformeringen tillater signerer å lage et sammendrag (brukes til å opprette en digital signatur) ved hjelp av den kanoniske formen et XML-dokument.

trans-unit.source: A recipient can then verify the XML digital signature using the same canonical form of the XML document with the same transform.
trans-unit.target: En mottaker kan deretter bekrefte den digitale signaturen for XML med samme kanoniske form av XML-dokumentet med samme transformering.

trans-unit.source: Use the XmlDsigC14NTransform class when you need to sign an XML document that does not contain comments.
trans-unit.target: Bruk XmlDsigC14NTransform klassen når du skal registrere et XML-dokument som ikke inneholder kommentarer.

trans-unit.source: In most cases, a new instance of a canonicalization transform class is not required.
trans-unit.target: I de fleste tilfeller kreves ikke en ny forekomst av en adresser transformering klasse.

trans-unit.source: To specify a canonicalization transform, pass the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) that describes the transform to the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethod%2A> property, which is accessible from the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en adresser transformering, kan du sende Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) som beskriver transformering til den <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethod%2A>egenskapen som er tilgjengelig fra den <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A> </xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethod%2A>

trans-unit.source: To acquire a reference to the canonicalization transform, use the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethodObject%2A> property, which is accessible from the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: For å hente en referanse til adresser transformeringen, kan du bruke den <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethodObject%2A>egenskapen som er tilgjengelig fra den <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.SignedInfo%2A> </xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedInfo.CanonicalizationMethodObject%2A>

trans-unit.source: The URI that describes the XmlDsigC14NTransform class is defined by the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigC14NTransformUrl> field and the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigCanonicalizationUrl> field.
trans-unit.target: URIEN som beskriver XmlDsigC14NTransform klassen er definert av den <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigC14NTransformUrl>felt og <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigCanonicalizationUrl>felt.</xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigCanonicalizationUrl> </xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.XmlDsigC14NTransformUrl>

trans-unit.source: You would only need to create a new instance of a canonicalization transform class for manually hashing an XML document or for using your own canonicalization algorithm.
trans-unit.target: Du trenger bare å opprette en ny forekomst av en transformering klasse adresser for nummer manuelt et XML-dokument eller for å bruke din egen adresser-algoritmen.

trans-unit.source: For more information about the C14N transform, see Sections 6.5 and 6.6.1 of the XMLDSIG specification, which is available from the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) at www.w3.org/TR/xmldsig-core/.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon om C14N transformeringen, kan du se deler 6.5 og 6.6.1 av XMLDSIG-spesifikasjonen, som er tilgjengelig fra World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) på www.w3.org/TR/xmldsig-core/.

trans-unit.source: The canonicalization algorithm is defined in the W3C Canonical XML specification, which is available at www.w3.org/TR/xml-c14n.
trans-unit.target: Algoritmen adresser er definert i den kanoniske W3C-XML-spesifikasjonen, som er tilgjengelig på www.w3.org/TR/xml-c14n.
